The Police have said that the documentation of recruits in Police Training Colleges/Schools in the ongoing 2020 recruitment of Constables into the Nigeria Police will close on Sunday. CP Frank Mba, the Force Public Relations Officer, made this known in a statement on Monday. Mba, who said that the training exercise began on Monday, warned that any candidate who failed to report within the specified period would be considered to have declined the offer. The Police PRO urged candidates who participated in the medical screening exercise in the recruitment exercise to check their recruitment status on the recruitment portal, www.policerecruitment.gov.ng. He called on successful candidates to print out their invitation slip and go to the Police Training College/School indicated for their names. Mba congratulated the successful candidates and urged them to check the recruitment portal for further information and directives that would aid their preparations in reporting for the training.